    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-08-23T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-08-23T15:00:00-05:00" n="967"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d967">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 860d.00/255</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Helsingfors</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HT2" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Haynes</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="2" xml:id="d967fn2">
                        <hi rend="italic">Id</hi>. (No. 1037).</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-08-23T16:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 23, 1918, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your 73. Department concurs in your opinion and commends your judgment that any
                    action or consultations relative to recognition of <hi rend="italic">de
                        facto</hi> government should be deferred until situation is more clearly
                    defined than at present.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
